article.headline: Miami (FL) 96, Alcorn State 57
article.story: CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Jack McClinton scored 21 points to lead Miami to a 96-57 win over Alcorn State Tuesday. Miami went on a 19-0 run in the first half and held Alcorn State without a field goal for 12 minutes. Miami (2-0) led 27-22 at the 10-minute mark of the first half before scoring the next 19 points. The Hurricanes took a 51-25 into halftime. Alcorn State (0-3) missed 15 consecutive shots before Delvin Thompson made a layup at the 17:33 mark of the second half. Miami shot 52 percent from the floor while holding Alcorn State to 34-percent. Brian Asbury's 15 first-half point paced the Hurricanes in the early going. Miami's Anthony Harris tied a career-high with 10 assists. McClinton also had six assists. Thompson came into the game averaging 21 points per game for the Braves and finished with 13 to lead the team.
